args:
With the prelims complete, the competition
begins for real! Mitsuba and Picaro make it
out of the first round and go head-to-head,
but an unknown rascal spikes Mitsuba's dashi
with excess salt, causing her elimination and
leading to bitter tears of regret.

And now, the kitchen warriors who were
victorious in the preliminaries will remain
in the Hungerdome as our next round
heats up like a mouthful of ghost chilies!

Amidst the flambé flames can be glimpsed
a dream—a vision of glory! But who will
brave those fires of flavor to emerge as
the greatest in the world?!
From group three, the winner of the second\nqualifier match is...Mitsuba!
And the winner of group six is...Valerio!
Wooo! Mitsuba and Valerio are\ncookin' with gas now!
And from group four, our victor is...Picaro!
That Picaro guy ain't no slouch.
I guess his win today means he and\nMitsuba will face off tomorrow, yeah?
I'm curious how their match will go.\nPicaro is the favorite, but Mitsuba is\ndoing this to fulfill an important dream.
*sip* Oh yeah, this dashi is PERFECT.\nThere's no way I'll lose tomorrow!
*sip* Mellow aroma... Slight tang...\nYes, this IS a splendid dashi.
Hey! Stay outta my soup pot, you!\nWhat are you doing here, anyway?\nScouting out your future competition?
Not at all. I was merely curious.
I had my suspicions when I glimpsed your\nfamily crest, but now having tasted your\ndashi, I am convinced beyond all doubt.
You are from the Nanakusa family—\noperators of the famed traditional\nHinomotoan restaurant of the same name.
Holy crap, you know your stuff!\nAnd yeah, I'm their third daughter.

I had the chance once to sample your
family's cooking during a sojourn in
Hinomoto, and was nearly moved to tears.
How does your establishment fare?
Er, the founder—my father—he...\nHe passed away.
But with my siblings' help, we were\nable to get the restaurant reopened.
It was tough getting all seven of us to\nwork together. And then, we had an even\nlarger issue rear its ugly head.
It seems none of us can perfectly\nrecreate the flavors of our father.
As a result, our customer base is shrinking.\nWe're okay for the moment, but if things\ndon't turn around soon...
And while I can't reproduce my father's\nflavors perfectly, I CAN create new food\nthat inherits its appeal.
People call my father's food the best in\nHinomoto, but I've come here to win\nthis contest and SURPASS his flavors!
My siblings are all counting on me.\nOur entire future rests on this.
You said you came here to make a dream\ncome true, right?
Well, my reason for cooking is bigger than\na mere ＂dream.＂
If it is a fight you seek, take your fervor\nand throw it at your opponent tomorrow.\nTrust me, you will need all of it.
I don't need YOU to tell me that!
Mmm, indeed. Well then, I've my own\npreparations to attend to, so... Ah.
Tch. I forgot a hair tie. What a hassle.
You tie it back in the kitchen, eh?\nHow unexpectedly conscientious.
You'll not get into my head\nso easily as all that!
Just use that blue ribbon you've got\ntied around your sword.
...N-no. It's fine. I will simply go to\nmy room and retrieve another.
Well, THAT got strange fast. What's so\nimportant about a little blue ribbon?\n...Eh, whatever. Not my problem.
Now then. While the dashi cools, I'll make\na little trip to the vegetable storehouse.
At last, Mitsuba versus Picaro!\nI wonder how it's gonna go?
Mitsuba is making Hinomotoan cuisine\nwith her special dashi, but Picaro has\nhigh-class cuisine and money to burn.
Both of 'em sound delicious to me!\nI mean, if we ignore the fact that\nthat Picaro guy is a total chump.
The match is single-elimination.\nWho will make it to the final round?
And now, we have Nanakusa's Mitsuba\nversus L'Amandier's Picaro!
Who will be the one to snatch victory\nfrom the searing-hot pan of conflict?!\nAh, and there goes Mitsuba!
She's taken out a massive pot filled with...\nYes, it's her famed Hinomotoan dashi!\nShe's sampling for taste...
Oh no! Chef Mitsuba looks upset!
Oho, I DO hope some scoundrel has\nnot slipped extra salt into your dashi!
By my blessed pizza peel! Surely you are\nnot accusing me of such a horrid act\nwithout any proof whatsoever?

Now, if you are done with these baseless
accusations, let us see if your salty dashi
can defeat my vastly superior flavors.
Oho! Oho ho ho ho ho!
(Gya! This dashi is totally ruined!\nOkay, Mitsuba, think. Think!\nYou need a Plan B, pronto!)
(If I can't manage to do something\nwith a setback like this, I'll never\nbe able to surpass Dad.)
(On the honor of Nanakusa,\nI WILL win this!)
Our judges have completed their tasting!
Now they will hold up placards and inform\nus who they believe the winner to be.\nLet the judging...BEGIIIIN!
Be Mitsuba, be Mitsuba, be Mitsuba...
One vote, Mitsuba! Another vote, Mitsuba!\nOne vote, Picaro!
Another Picaro, aaaaand...PICARO!\nPicaro has done it! He is the winner!
Oho ho! Shout all you like, little one.\nAll of your hot air will not make your\ndishes any less limp and uninspired.
HOWEVER! Let us, for the moment,\npretend your inane accusation is correct\nand I did slip salt into your dashi.

A true chef could have recovered from
such an incident. They could have found
a way to balance their flavors and save
the day. Yet you did not.
Did he really put salt in your dashi?
He must have. Just look at him smirk!\nI...I don't know what I'm going to do...
How can I ever face my siblings again?\nOh, Dad would be so disappointed...
It's a damn dirty trick, but we ain't got a\nshred'a proof he's the one what did it.
It doesn't matter. He's right. A skilled chef\nwould have been able to recover from it.
I just... I wanted to win so much...
I warned you to be careful of that man,\ndid I not, chef? Still, despite the trickery,\nnone who know can doubt your skill.

You may not be the champion this day,
but I think you have the skill to restore
Nanakusa to its former glory. So...er...
do not give in to despair?
You might be top-class when it comes\nto cooking, but you sorta suck when it\ncomes to comforting people.
What?! But I came here specifically\nto make you feel better!
Yeah, well, you're not doing it right,\nand now I'm just getting sadder. *sniff*
And this is why I loathe such endeavors...
Well, I can't say I don't like Picaro's guts\nto do whatever it takes to win...
But I will never condone the intentional\nruining of food—especially when it is\nbeing served to others!
It looks as though I must teach Picaro\nthe secret to being a chef...with one\nof my greatest dishes!
